      <h1 class='title'>House of Lords: Recess Dates</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 14 October 2004 vol 665 c25WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_25ws' title='Col. 25WS &mdash; HL Deb 14 October 2004 vol 665 c25WS' name='column_25ws' href='#column_25ws' rel='bookmark'>25WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0665P0-09485'>
        <a name='S5LV0665P0_20041014_LWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-bruce-grocott' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041014_LWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Mr Bruce Grocott' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-bruce-grocott" title="Mr Bruce Grocott">Lord Grocott</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0665P0-09485">At Commons Business Questions today, my right honourable friend Peter Hain MP announced the following provisional recess dates for the House of Commons:</p><p id="S5LV0665P0-09486"><span class="italic">Christmas</span>
          <ul>
          <li>Rise close of play&#x2014;Tuesday 21 December</li>
          <li>Return&#x2014;Monday 10 January</li>
          </ul></p><p id="S5LV0665P0-09487"><span class="italic">Constituency week</span>
          <ul>
          <li>Rise close of play&#x2014;Thursday 10 February</li>
          <li>Return&#x2014;Monday 21 February</li>
          </ul></p><p id="S5LV0665P0-09488"><span class="italic">Easter</span>
          <ul>
          <li>Rise close of play&#x2014;Thursday 24 March</li>
          <li>Return&#x2014;Monday 4 April</li>
          </ul></p><p id="S5LV0665P0-09489"><span class="italic">Whitsun</span>
          <ul>
          <li>Rise close of play&#x2014;Thursday 26 May</li>
          <li>Return&#x2014;Monday 6 June</li>
          </ul></p><p id="S5LV0665P0-09490"><span class="italic">Summer</span>
          <ul>
          <li>Rise close of play&#x2014;Thursday 28 July</li>
          <li>Return&#x2014;Monday 10 October</li>
          </ul></p><p id="S5LV0665P0-09491">It is my intention to match these dates for the House of Lords, subject of course to the requirements and progress of business.</p><p id="S5LV0665P0-09492">It is not proposed to have a September sitting next year, because work needs to be done in the Commons Chamber.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
